The paper proposes an algorithm for EEG source identification using dictionary learning methods applied in the covariance-domain. This involves leveraging techniques from machine learning (specifically, dictionary learning) to solve a problem in neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves signal processing and analysis, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing). The use of covariance-domain methods suggests a potential fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper involves human subjects and EEG experiments, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
